===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|dormous|lang=enm}}, of uncertain origin. Possibly from {{term||dor-|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{term|dár||benumbed|lang=non}} + {{term|mous||mouse|lang=enm}}. More at {{l|en|doze}}, {{l|en|mouse}}.

The word is sometimes considered to come from an {{etyl|xno|-}} derivative of {{etyl|fro|-}} {{term|dormir||to sleep|lang=fro}}, but no such Anglo-Norman word is known to have existed. <ref>Random House Dictionary, dormouse.</ref>

===Pronunciation===
